    cve:description "Predictable TCP sequence numbers allow spoofing." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0077" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0082> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "CWD ~root command in ftpd allows root access." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0082" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0084> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Certain NFS servers allow users to use mknod to gain privileges by creating a writable kmem device and setting the UID to 0." ;
    cve:hasCWE "sepses:CWE-269" ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0084" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0095> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The debug command in Sendmail is enabled, allowing attackers to execute commands as root." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0095" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0113> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Some implementations of rlogin allow root access if given a -froot parameter." ;
    cve:hasCWE "sepses:CWE-88" ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0113" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0117> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "AIX passwd allows local users to gain root access." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0117" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0120> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Sun/Solaris utmp file allows local users to gain root access if it is writable by users other than root." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0120" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0124> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Vulnerabilities in UMN gopher and gopher+ versions 1.12 and 2.0x allow an intruder to read any files that can be accessed by the gopher daemon." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0124" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0145> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Sendmail WIZ command enabled, allowing root access." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0145" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0151> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The SATAN session key may be disclosed if the user points the web browser to other sites, possibly allowing root access." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0151" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0155> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The ghostscript command with the -dSAFER option allows remote attackers to execute commands." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0155" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0161> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "In Cisco IOS 10.3, with the tacacs-ds or tacacs keyword, an extended IP access control list could bypass filtering." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0161" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0164> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "A race condition in the Solaris ps command allows an attacker to overwrite critical files." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0164" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0167> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "In SunOS, NFS file handles could be guessed, giving unauthorized access to the exported file system." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0167" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0168> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The portmapper may act as a proxy and redirect service requests from an attacker, making the request appear to come from the local host, possibly bypassing authentication that would otherwise have taken place.  For example, NFS file systems could be mounted through the portmapper despite export restrictions." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0168" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0172> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "FormMail CGI program allows remote execution of commands." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0172" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0181> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The wall daemon can be used for denial of service, social engineering attacks, or to execute remote commands." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0181" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0203> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "In Sendmail, attackers can gain root privileges via SMTP by specifying an improper \"mail from\" address and an invalid \"rcpt to\" address that would cause the mail to bounce to a program." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0203" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0207> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Remote attacker can execute commands through Majordomo using the Reply-To field and a \"lists\" command." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0207" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0209> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "The SunView (SunTools) selection_svc facility allows remote users to read files." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0209" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/cve/CVE-1999-0211> a cve:CVE ;
    cve:description "Extra long export lists over 256 characters in some mount daemons allows NFS directories to be mounted by anyone." ;
    cve:id "CVE-1999-0211" .

